    "body": "Note: too verbose to include in `--startuptime` by default, but I wanted detailed profiling to work on optimizing the separate steps.\r\n\r\nProvides lines in startuptime for\r\n- `require'my.module' lookup/parse` total time of the `require` loader (returns the loaded module as an unexecuted function\r\n- `require'my.module' execute` actually executing the code inside the module (should be very fast if it just defines a module of functions)\r\n- `rtp lookup: ...` any use of nvim_get_runtime_file (runs nested within lookup/parse for a lua require).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Just tried this. Gets me from 300ms->215ms, so a pretty big improvement really.\n\nThe main benefit of this is that it should mean plugin authors will need to worry a lot less about using `require`.",
